# Long session hygiene (requestable)

When context may be stale:

1. Use Workflow Cannon MCP first for fresh reload/session context when available; otherwise open **`.ai/LONG-SESSION-RELOAD.md`** (agent checklist).
2. Use MCP first for queue/task status reads when the tool can prove freshness; otherwise run `pnpm run wk doctor` and `pnpm run wk run get-next-actions '{}'` from repo root (do not insert `pnpm`'s `--` between `wk` and `run`).
3. Do not trust chat memory for task `status`; use MCP reads or task-engine CLI reads.
4. Maintainer narrative (optional): `.ai/runbooks/cursor-long-session.md` (human render under `docs/maintainers/runbooks/` when regenerated).
